===政界===
袭击发生后，斯蒂芬·哈珀总理向各部长通报情况。国会议员马克·加诺和[[约翰·麦凯|约翰·麦凯]]作出及时反映。渥太华市长吉姆·沃森称这是“本国和本市悲惨的一天<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-29724907?ns_mchannel=social&ns_campaign=bbc_breaking&ns_source=twitter&ns_linkname=news_central|title=BBC News – Ottawa shootings: Soldier killed and city on lockdown|work=BBC News|accessdate=2014-10-22|archive-date=2014-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025065131/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-29724907?ns_mchannel=social&ns_campaign=bbc_breaking&ns_source=twitter&ns_linkname=news_central|dead-url=no}}</ref>”。加拿大政坛其他人士和社交媒体亦作出回应<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cp24.com/news/reaction-how-canadian-politicians-are-reacting-to-the-tragedy-in-ottawa-1.2065916|title=REACTION: How Canadian politicians are reacting to the tragedy in Ottawa|work=CP24|accessdate=2014-10-22|archive-date=2014-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204074156/http://www.cp24.com/news/reaction-how-canadian-politicians-are-reacting-to-the-tragedy-in-ottawa-1.2065916|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

哈珀在当晚的电视讲话中，称枪击案是“野蛮的暴力袭击<ref name="harperspeech">{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com.au/canadian-prime-minister-stephen-harper-the-parliament-shooting-was-a-terrorist-attack-2014-10|title=Canadian Prime Minister Stephen Harper: The Parliament Shooting Was a Terrorist Attack|author=Peter Terlato|work=[[Business_Insider|Business Insider Australia]]|date=2014-10-22|accessdate=2014-10-23|archive-date=2014-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141023020522/http://www.businessinsider.com.au/canadian-prime-minister-stephen-harper-the-parliament-shooting-was-a-terrorist-attack-2014-10|dead-url=yes}}</ref>”，还特别提到了案发数日前，帕特里斯·文森特准尉遭ISIL风格恐怖袭击遇害的案件<ref name=auto1>{{Cite news|url = http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/ottawa-shooting-harper-mulcair-trudeau-speak-about-attack-1.2809530|title = Ottawa shooting: Harper, Mulcair, Trudeau speak about attack|date = 2014-10-23|work = CBC News|accessdate = 2014-10-24|archive-date = 2014-10-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141023091350/http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/ottawa-shooting-harper-mulcair-trudeau-speak-about-attack-1.2809530|dead-url = no}}</ref>。哈珀坚称，加拿大不会被暴力行径吓倒，并将继续致力于与世界各地的盟友紧密合作，打击残酷对待其他国家，希望将野蛮行为带到我国的恐怖组织。她们将不会有安全的避风港<ref name=auto1/>。案发翌日，哈珀表示要加快增加安全部队布控、拘留和逮捕权力的计划<ref name=emotional>{{cite web|url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/mps-return-to-house-in-emotional-gathering-after-ottawa-shooting/article21263777/|title="Harper vows to strengthen national security laws after Ottawa shooting", by Bill Curry and Kathryn Blaze Carlson, ''The Globe and Mail''|work=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=2014-10-24|archive-date=2014-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141023183531/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/mps-return-to-house-in-emotional-gathering-after-ottawa-shooting/article21263777/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。10月23日，在向下议院发表演说时，将本周的两起袭击归类为恐怖活动，他表示：“我们深知并深受本周两起由加拿大公民、生长在这个和平国度的年轻人所执行的恐怖袭击的困扰<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.gc.ca/web/article-en.do;jsessionid=0d42a58367c5507c37839a9acf8a4ffd53d26f455439244e581c077f878ae144.e38RbhaLb3qNe38Lchr0?mthd=index&crtr.page=1&nid=896349|title=Statement by the Prime Minister of Canada|accessdate=2014-10-23|archive-date=2014-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024054220/http://news.gc.ca/web/article-en.do;jsessionid=0d42a58367c5507c37839a9acf8a4ffd53d26f455439244e581c077f878ae144.e38RbhaLb3qNe38Lchr0?mthd=index&crtr.page=1&nid=896349|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

反对党新民主党领袖[[唐民凯|唐民凯]]在袭击事件发生后发表公开声明，他表示：“正如我们所有人见证的这些恐怖行为，我们敬畏你那英勇的行为，守法是当今加拿大的力量、价值观和勇气来源。”加拿大自由党领袖[[贾斯汀·特鲁多|贾斯汀·特鲁多]]部分支出：“加拿大人知道以伊斯兰教为名的行动是（穆斯林）信仰的畸变。相互尊重和钦佩有助于防止被扭曲的伪宗教意识形态宣传的影响<ref name=auto1/>。”[[加拿大绿党|加拿大绿党]]领袖[[伊丽莎白·梅伊|伊丽莎白·梅伊]]在下议院表示，“我会把钱押在这些由问题人士造成的孤立、令人不安和深受困扰的疯狂行动上。我不相信这个恐怖网络很庞大，或是本国今天的风险比上周又要加强。但这终究是我的看法。我可能错了，我毫无疑问会再次出错，但我建议，在等待警方答复之前，我们要做出假设，从容、真实说话并向所有加拿大人公开。”但《[[环球邮报|环球邮报]]》称她的讲话遭到了地面两派的抱怨声<ref name=emotional/>。

[[安大略省省长|安大略省省长]][[凯斯琳·韦恩|凯斯琳·韦恩]]表示：“我们的信念是，那些想用暴力手段破坏民主的人们要求我们保持沉默，但我们拒绝封口<ref>{{cite news|script-title=en:‘We refuse to be silenced': Ontario premier Kathleen Wynne defiant in face of Ottawa shooting|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/2014/10/22/we-refuse-to-be-silenced-ontario-premier-kathleen-wynne-defiant-in-face-of-ottawa-shooting/|accessdate=2014-10-22|work=National Post|agency=Canadian Press|date=2014-10-22|archive-date=2014-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022232019/http://news.nationalpost.com/2014/10/22/we-refuse-to-be-silenced-ontario-premier-kathleen-wynne-defiant-in-face-of-ottawa-shooting/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Artuso|first1=Antonella|script-title=en:Kathleen Wynne: ‘We refuse to be silenced’|url=http://www.sunnewsnetwork.ca/sunnews/politics/archives/2014/10/20141022-121832.html|accessdate=2014-10-22|work=Sun News Network|agency=QMI Agency|date=2014-10-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022224403/http://www.sunnewsnetwork.ca/sunnews/politics/archives/2014/10/20141022-121832.html|archivedate=2014-10-22}}</ref>。”当天阿尔伯塔立法会的公众参观取消，安保升级<ref name=alberta/>。作为防御措施，温哥华岛多数人选区办事处不列颠哥伦比亚省立法议会被限制访问<ref>{{cite news|title=Legislature, CFB Esquimalt on alert; MP offices closed|url=http://www.timescolonist.com/legislature-cfb-esquimalt-on-alert-mp-offices-closed-1.1453475|accessdate=2014-10-22|work=[[Victoria_Times-Colonist|Victoria Times-Colonist]]|date=2014-10-22|location=Victoria, British Columbia|archive-date=2014-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141023011702/http://www.timescolonist.com/legislature-cfb-esquimalt-on-alert-mp-offices-closed-1.1453475|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[新斯科舍省|新斯科舍省]]立法机关公公画廊仅限传媒、政界人士和工作人员访问<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thechronicleherald.ca/novascotia/1245528-nova-scotia-legislature-closed-to-public-after-shootings-in-ottawa|title=Nova Scotia legislature closed to public after shootings in Ottawa|work=The Chronicle Herald|accessdate=2014-10-25|archive-date=2014-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025110326/http://thechronicleherald.ca/novascotia/1245528-nova-scotia-legislature-closed-to-public-after-shootings-in-ottawa|dead-url=no}}</ref>。10月22日，魁北克国民议会下半旗，向西里洛致哀<ref name="#1"/>。

